abstract: Insanity, which is an exceptional state of the mind, and of comparatively rare occurrence, has come to be one of the most common pleas in defence of crime. Cases are constantly occurring in which perpetrators of the most shocking homicides are acquitted on the ground that they were insane, and, therefore, not responsible for their acts when the deed was committed.
